<D>__{we missed the best of it, didn't we, pal?}
<A>__{both men laugh a little lewdly.}
<C>__{pilot}
<D>__{she ran off to mexico. rumor was she was knocked up and didn't even know who the father was. went there to get rid of it.}
<C>__{gittes}
<D>__{you don't say?}
<C>__{pilot}
<D>__{cross was looking for her all over the country. offered rewards, everything. felt real sorry for him, with all his money.}
<B>__{albacore club day}
<A>__{a pleasant but unobtrusive clapboard blue and white building on the bay overlooking the harbor. the seaplane lands. a motor launch with a burgee of a fish flying from it turns and heads in the direction of the plane.}
